					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This is dated merely in the cyclic year Raudri without giving its Śaka equivalent. It records a decision of Daḷavāy Vaiyappa-Nāyakkar, the agent of Timmappa-Nāyakkar, and the managers of the temple of Tirumeyyam Malaiyāḷaṉ, that the income from Iruñjiṟaiyūr which was a <hi rend="italic">tiruviḍaiyāṭṭam</hi> village of the god was to be utilised (in future solely) for the repairs of the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
